1
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:46,090
[THE HUNT]

2
00:02:21,079 --> 00:02:22,280
Tomorrow morning,

3
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:22,530
come with me to your husband's family.

4
00:02:22,530 --> 00:02:25,079
[1987, Baorong Village, Nanyang Province]

5
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:26,940
You don't need to bring anything.

6
00:02:27,310 --> 00:02:29,710
They're afraid of your late husband's
spirit,

7
00:02:29,710 --> 00:02:31,400
so they won't let you
bring anything there.

8
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:31,960
Otherwise, he might

9
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,750
follow you there to seek vengeance

10
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:34,870
and cause trouble.

11
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,220
That wouldn't be good.

12
00:02:36,310 --> 00:02:37,579
I mean my son.

13
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,160
He's a boy.

14
00:02:39,190 --> 00:02:41,050
Of course you can bring him there.

15
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:44,650
When you get there,

16
00:02:44,710 --> 00:02:46,360
you’ll stay in an unused room
for one night.

17
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:47,400
The day after tomorrow,
you'll get married—

18
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,460
without a banquet.

19
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:50,360
So that's the plan.

20
00:02:50,590 --> 00:02:51,430
Tomorrow morning,

21
00:02:51,430 --> 00:02:53,000
I'll pick her up at the village entrance.

22
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,200
Thank you, Mrs. Zhou.

23
00:02:54,310 --> 00:02:55,150
Let me walk you out.

24
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:56,680
It's okay.

25
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:04,470
Mom!

26
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,560
Mom, don't go!

27
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:08,080
Mom!

28
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:12,800
Mom, wait for me!

29
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:14,800
Take me with you!

30
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:15,800
Mom!

31
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:17,740
Mom, don't go!

32
00:03:17,870 --> 00:03:18,800
Mom, wait for me!

33
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:20,079
Take me with you!

34
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:21,840
Ximei! Ximei! Ximei!

35
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:23,840
Mom!

36
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:25,630
Mom, don't go!

37
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,570
Mom!

38
00:03:27,630 --> 00:03:28,840
Mom, wait for me!

39
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:31,220
I will come back to see you in a few days.

40
00:03:31,430 --> 00:03:32,870
Be a good girl.

41
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,540
Listen to Grandma

42
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:35,980
and Uncle.

43
00:03:36,079 --> 00:03:37,360
A bride doesn't look back

44
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,590
so she won't bring bad luck.

45
00:03:38,590 --> 00:03:39,840
Let's go.

46
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:41,300
Your mom

47
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,970
is going to her new home
for a better life.

48
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,200
Be a good girl, Ximei.

49
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:46,900
I'm not being good!

50
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:47,750
Otherwise, why did Mom

51
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:49,680
only take my little brother

52
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,470
but not me?

53
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:53,210
Ximei, you're a big girl now.

54
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,380
You should be a good girl.

55
00:03:54,380 --> 00:03:56,180
I don't want to be a good girl!

56
00:03:56,180 --> 00:03:56,430
[Behind her, flames are burning;]

57
00:03:56,430 --> 00:03:57,750
I want my mom!

58
00:03:58,030 --> 00:03:58,350
Mom, come back!

59
00:03:58,350 --> 00:04:01,020
[before her, the dawn is rising.]

60
00:04:01,090 --> 00:04:03,760
[Old Days: Episode 2]

61
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:11,400
[1996, Baorong Village, Nanyang Province]

62
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,540
It's okay. I'll handle it.

63
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:42,430
Fuchang is a good boy.

64
00:04:42,740 --> 00:04:44,120
He helps out.

65
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:56,670
Fuchang's face is so dark,

66
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,480
like a dark-skinned sugarcane.

67
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:00,680
You're a black-skinned sugarcane too.

68
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:01,990
You're laughing?

69
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:03,950
You're just too honest.

70
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:05,950
Whatever others say, you accept it.

71
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:20,810
If you ask me,

72
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:21,840
that Guo Adi

73
00:05:21,870 --> 00:05:23,040
is an honest man.

74
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,750
He has a wife.

75
00:05:25,020 --> 00:05:26,630
He had a wife.

76
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:27,630
But now…

77
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,160
didn't she run away?

78
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,240
She ran away to escape his beatings.

79
00:05:34,159 --> 00:05:35,140
Some people say

80
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,780
his wife was beaten to death by him

81
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:39,510
and buried somewhere.

82
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,800
That's just the villagers

83
00:05:42,870 --> 00:05:44,380
spreading rumors because they're jealous

84
00:05:44,380 --> 00:05:45,450
of his money.

85
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:48,020
He stinks. His house stinks even more.

86
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:50,190
You can smell it from far away.

87
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:51,890
That's because he dries fish powder

88
00:05:51,890 --> 00:05:53,530
at home.

89
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:54,970
If you don't like it, just tell him not to

90
00:05:54,970 --> 00:05:56,780
after you marry him.

91
00:05:57,310 --> 00:05:59,240
He'll definitely listen to you.

92
00:05:59,310 --> 00:05:59,820
I won't marry him.

93
00:05:59,820 --> 00:06:01,620
I won't marry him no matter what.

94
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:03,220
Say that again!

95
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:04,410
Auntie.

96
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:07,390
Well...

97
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:09,680
Ximei,

98
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:11,120
back then, your mom

99
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,790
just up and left.

100
00:06:13,070 --> 00:06:14,290
Our family raised you,

101
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:15,580
and it wasn't easy.

102
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,160
You should repay our kindness.

103
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:20,120
Decai is getting married.

104
00:06:20,270 --> 00:06:21,330
If you don't marry,

105
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:23,110
how can he?

106
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:25,640
He's your cousin.

107
00:06:25,870 --> 00:06:26,690
That's right.

108
00:06:26,830 --> 00:06:27,430
Do you plan

109
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:28,950
to live off this family

110
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,270
for your whole life?

111
00:06:30,290 --> 00:06:31,010
Women

112
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,830
have to get married eventually.

113
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:33,680
You sold my mom,

114
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,140
and now you're selling me!

115
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,090
What are you talking about?

116
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,140
They've already prepared

117
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:40,220
the bride price.

118
00:06:40,310 --> 00:06:41,390
You guys make the choice yourselves.

119
00:06:41,390 --> 00:06:42,510
I'm done with this matter.

120
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:42,920
Mrs. Zhou.

121
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:43,520
Mrs. Zhou!

122
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:44,720
Mrs. Zhou!

123
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,250
Don't go, Mrs. Zhou!

124
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:47,310
Mrs. Zhou!

125
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,310
Auntie.

126
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:52,890
If I have to get married,
I'll marry Fuchang.

127
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:53,720
Fuchang?

128
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,450
What's so good about Fuchang?

129
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:57,290
His family is so poor

130
00:06:57,290 --> 00:06:59,120
he can't even afford pants.

131
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,780
And he's mute.

132
00:07:01,390 --> 00:07:03,260
He can't even afford the engagement money.

133
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:05,480
You'll be poor your whole life with him.

134
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:07,430
I'm not afraid of being poor.

135
00:07:07,630 --> 00:07:09,060
If I have to get married,
I'll marry Fuchang.

136
00:07:09,060 --> 00:07:10,700
You think you have a choice?

137
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,020
You're so young,

138
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:15,220
and you want to choose your own husband?

139
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,120
Shameless.

140
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:20,330
I know you don't want to get married
right now,

141
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,420
but from your grandma to your mom,

142
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:24,360
including your auntie—

143
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:25,950
haven't all the women

144
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:27,950
gotten through it the same way?

145
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:29,500
Be good.

146
00:07:30,070 --> 00:07:30,870
In the future,

147
00:07:30,890 --> 00:07:32,340
once you have a child,

148
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,159
you will

149
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:34,810
gradually settle down.

150
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:41,090
You're young

151
00:07:41,390 --> 00:07:42,510
and beautiful.

152
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:45,030
You'll live better

153
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:46,780
than your grandma

154
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:47,920
and your mom.

155
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:05,290
Pay your respects to your grandma

156
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,360
one last time.

157
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,040
After the mourning period,

158
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:08,980
just marry him.

159
00:08:19,350 --> 00:08:20,800
Be good, Ximei.

160
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:22,890
Listen to your uncle.

161
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:25,390
It's all for your own good.

162
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:28,430
Wu Ximei.

163
00:08:30,390 --> 00:08:31,000
Wu Ximei.

164
00:08:38,150 --> 00:08:39,750
We've checked your records.

165
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:40,960
You and Cao Xiaojun

166
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,890
registered your marriage in 2004.

167
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:43,789
Why did you say

168
00:08:43,789 --> 00:08:45,080
you got married at 16?

169
00:08:58,270 --> 00:09:00,270
Actually, Xiaojun...

170
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:03,120
was my 2nd husband.

171
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:06,400
I was

172
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:08,750
married once before.

173
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,390
No more drinking!

174
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:39,440
If I drink more,

175
00:10:39,510 --> 00:10:41,200
it'll ruin my good day.

176
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,480
I'll come to your place tomorrow,

177
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,570
and we'll drink then,

178
00:10:44,570 --> 00:10:45,440
okay?

179
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,550
Stop looking! Stop looking!

180
00:10:51,550 --> 00:10:52,490
Go!

181
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:53,880
Don't look anymore.

182
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:16,320
What's that pillow for?

183
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:22,560
I heard when remarrying,

184
00:11:23,670 --> 00:11:24,830
on the first night,

185
00:11:27,470 --> 00:11:30,470
you need to place a pillow
for the first wife's spirit.

186
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,630
And we're not supposed to…

187
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:34,910
The first wife's spirit? Nonsense!

188
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,390
What a bad omen.

189
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:46,710
Take off your clothes.

190
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:49,550
These need to be returned tomorrow.

191
00:11:58,600 --> 00:11:59,870
Take them off!

192
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,100
I was still young back then.

193
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:15,360
We couldn't get a marriage certificate.

194
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:16,610
We just

195
00:12:16,870 --> 00:12:18,470
had a small wedding banquet.

196
00:12:20,630 --> 00:12:21,940
Thinking about it now,

197
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:22,970
I was really

198
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,130
a gambler back then.

199
00:12:25,910 --> 00:12:27,000
I staked my whole life

200
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,480
on Guo Adi,

201
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:31,770
betting that...

202
00:12:32,670 --> 00:12:33,800
he had a conscience,

203
00:12:33,890 --> 00:12:35,350
that he would be grateful,

204
00:12:35,910 --> 00:12:37,440
that he would treat me well.

205
00:12:38,270 --> 00:12:38,910
And?

206
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,080
I won the bet.

207
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:44,050
He treated me very well.

208
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,580
He gave me

209
00:12:49,670 --> 00:12:51,270
all the good food and drinks.

210
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:54,060
He cherished me dearly

211
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,960
and never hurt me.

212
00:12:59,070 --> 00:13:01,150
Of course, we bickered sometimes.

213
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,260
Living together is like

214
00:13:02,260 --> 00:13:04,180
using a spoon to stir in a pot—

215
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:07,080
there are always little bumps.

216
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,840
My grandma once told me,

217
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:15,870
"Suffering is a blessing.

218
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:17,630
Just endure it

219
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,000
in this life;

220
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,740
it will be better in the next."

221
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:54,760
You went to the village clinic, right?

222
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:56,480
What did He say?

223
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:00,870
Well...

224
00:14:01,910 --> 00:14:02,600
He said

225
00:14:02,630 --> 00:14:04,220
I might not be getting enough nutrition
lately,

226
00:14:04,220 --> 00:14:05,680
so my period is irregular.

227
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:08,880
So you're not pregnant?

228
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:17,110
He's just a village doctor.

229
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,390
He knows nothing.

230
00:14:18,970 --> 00:14:20,320
You should go to the town hospital

231
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,380
in a couple of days.

232
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:23,830
Oh,

233
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:25,910
when I was visiting the family graves,

234
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,150
I caught a gecko.

235
00:14:28,150 --> 00:14:28,960
Later, take out that bottle

236
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:29,840
at home for making liquor

237
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:30,870
and wash it.

238
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,000
This afternoon,

239
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,030
I'll buy some double-distilled liquor

240
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:34,150
and make medicinal wine myself.

241
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:34,600
Okay.

242
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:07,640
Buddha, please bless us.

243
00:16:09,270 --> 00:16:10,910
Bless Guo Adi to be kind,

244
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,630
so I can have some peaceful days.

245
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:29,740
Adi, have some tea.

246
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:32,630
Tea?

247
00:16:34,140 --> 00:16:35,080
Do you know how people outside

248
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:36,120
laugh at me?

249
00:16:36,450 --> 00:16:37,750
Why can't you have a child?

250
00:16:37,750 --> 00:16:38,670
Why can't you?

251
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:40,390
You know, if you can't give me a son,

252
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:42,510
you won't even be buried
in our ancestral grave after death.

253
00:16:42,510 --> 00:16:44,440
Adi, I'll go to town tomorrow.

254
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:45,670
Come with me.

255
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:47,190
You think there's something wrong with me?

256
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:48,390
What's wrong with me?

257
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:49,720
What's wrong with me?

258
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:50,790
What's wrong with me?

259
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:51,750
You think it's my problem, right?

260
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:52,720
What nonsense

261
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:53,790
did you

262
00:16:53,810 --> 00:16:54,490
hear about me?

263
00:16:54,490 --> 00:16:56,060
What did those quack doctors say about me?

264
00:16:56,060 --> 00:16:56,900
Tell me!

265
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:58,360
What did they say?

266
00:16:58,550 --> 00:17:00,290
You can't have children.

267
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,140
So why did I even marry you?

268
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:03,240
It's not me!

269
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,430
What's not you?

270
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:05,349
Tell me!

271
00:17:06,109 --> 00:17:06,940
Didn't your previous wife

272
00:17:06,940 --> 00:17:08,339
fail to get pregnant too?

273
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:09,900
If you want a child,

274
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:11,730
Adi, let's go to the hospital together.

275
00:17:11,730 --> 00:17:13,150
Let's go together, okay?

276
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,300
Go to the hospital?

277
00:17:14,310 --> 00:17:15,510
What's wrong with me?

278
00:17:16,310 --> 00:17:17,109
Tell me!

279
00:17:17,130 --> 00:17:18,010
Xiang!

280
00:17:18,109 --> 00:17:18,790
Stop hitting her!

281
00:17:18,790 --> 00:17:20,050
If you keep hitting her, she'll die.

282
00:17:20,050 --> 00:17:20,569
Enough,

283
00:17:20,589 --> 00:17:21,829
Adi, if you beat your wife to death,

284
00:17:21,829 --> 00:17:22,530
no one will give you children.

285
00:17:22,530 --> 00:17:23,060
Get lost!

286
00:17:28,170 --> 00:17:29,870
Mind your own family's

287
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:31,540
business!

288
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:32,720
One day,

289
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:34,210
I'll beat you too!

290
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:35,490
Get lost!

291
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:46,660
